column1: //EzyFulfillment Order template v5.0
//Double slash in the beginning indicates they are instructions or guide
//Do NOT remove or modify rows 47 and 48. Do NOT alter the header name in row 47
//*Indicates required field
//First line of a new order must have all the mandatory fields filled
//All Item level field type must be repeated for each item. All Order level field type can be repeated to subsequent item lines or left blank
//All Order live items will be read from first order entry. Any information whether same or different in subsequent lines will be ignored
//For International Orders customs information must be repeated for all items in that order
//All blank fields for optional fields will use default values where applicable
//*Merchant Order ID - A unique identifier for the order, assigned by the merchant. Alphanumeric with maximum of 30 characters allowed
//*Customer First Name - Max 30 characters
//*Customer Last Name - Max 30 characters
//*Address 1 - Mandatory address line. Max. 60 characters
//Address 2 - Optional address line
//*Address City - The city of of the recipient's address
//Address State Or Region - The state of of the recipient's address
//*Address Country - The country code of of the recipient's address. Accepts Universal 2-letter country code only. Please refer to the complete list (https://www.iso.org/obp/ui/#search)
//*Address Postal Code - The postal (zip) code of the recipient's address
//Address Contact Phone - Contact number of the recipient
//Address Contact Email - Contact email of the recipient
//*Delivery Method - For Domestic, 1 - Standard, 2 - Economy. For International, 1 - Standard, 2 - Economy, 3 - Priority
//*Merchant SKU / FBSP-SKU ID - Only one SKU must be provided (either FBSP-SKU or Merchant SKU). The SKU must already be present in the catalog
//*Units - Unit added must be less than or equal to  quantity under Fulfillable status for this SKU. Positive integers only. Maximum quantity 100
//Customs Item description - Required only for international orders. If left empty, will take values from Product information. Fill this field to override the information for this order
//hs code - Harmonized System. Minimum 6 digits (Chapter, Heading, subheading) and upto 10. Please refer to the complete list (http://hts.usitc.gov)
//Country of Origin - Required only for international orders. Universal 2-letter country code. Please refer to the complete list (https://www.iso.org/obp/ui/#search)
//Per Unit Declared Value - Required only for international orders. If left empty, will take values from Product information. Fill this field to override the information for this order
//Declared Value Currency (XXX) - 3-letter currency code. Please refer to the complete list (http://iso4217.net)
//Enhanced Liability Taken (Y/N) - whether insurance is taken or not for enhanced liability coverage. Default value is N = No
//Enhanced Liability Amount (in SGD) - Furnish the amount in Singapore Dollars (SGD). Must be less than Declared value
//Category of Shipment (D, M, S, O) - Mandatory for international orders. D = Document, M = Merchandise, S = Sample & O = Others
//Description of Shipment - Mandatory when Category of Shipment is  chosen as Others. Provide a high level description of your Shipment
//Non Delivery Instructions (T, R) - Mandatory for international orders. T = Treat as Abandoned, R = Return to sender
//Automatically Approve after upload (Y/N) - whether the order is automatically approved for shipping. By default it is taken as No upon which needs approval by logging into the EZF Platform

//Displayable Order ID - The order id to be displayed on the packing slip.  This should match the order ID you provide to your customer. If empty merchant order ID is used. alphanumeric, hyphen (-). Max. 30 characters
//Displayable Order Date (DD/MM/YYYY) - The order date to display on the packing slip. Default is creation date. Date format DD/MM/YYYY
//Process Order Date (DD/MM/YYYY) - Advanced date at which the order should be processed. Cannot be more than one week from the current date. Default is approved date
//additional information 1-12 - These fields are for merchant's use. Their descriptive name can be edited by the merchant to suit their needs. In future these fields may be utilised by the platform.
merchant_order_id
*Merchant Order ID
column22: Category of Shipment (D, M, S, O)
